io.iron.ironmq

Class Queue

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.iron.ironmq.Queue

  • public class Queue
extends Object
    The Queue class represents a specific IronMQ queue bound to a client.

      • peek

        public Message peek()
             throws IOException
        Peeking at a queue returns the next messages on the queue, but it does not reserve them. If there are no items on the queue, an EmptyQueueException is thrown.
        Throws:
        EmptyQueueException - If the queue is empty.
        HTTPException - If the IronMQ service returns a status other than 200 OK.
        IOException - If there is an error accessing the IronMQ server.

      • peek

        public Messages peek(int numberOfMessages)
              throws IOException
        Peeking at a queue returns the next messages on the queue, but it does not reserve them.
        Parameters:
        numberOfMessages - The maximum number of messages to peek. Default is 1. Maximum is 100. Note: You may not receive all n messages on every request, the more sparse the queue, the less likely you are to receive all n messages.
        Throws:
        EmptyQueueException - If the queue is empty.
        HTTPException - If the IronMQ service returns a status other than 200 OK.
        IOException - If there is an error accessing the IronMQ server.

        errorQueue - The name of the error queue to use (can be null)
        retries - The retries.
        retriesDelay - The retries delay.
        Throws:
        HTTPException - If the IronMQ service returns a status other than 200 OK.
        IOException - If there is an error accessing the IronMQ server.
